_refine.details                                  
;THE PROTEIN CONSISTS OF RESIDUES 1 - 548.  RESIDUES 1 - 16
ARE ABSENT FROM THE ELECTRON DENSITY.  RESIDUES 17 - 24 ARE
MODELED, BUT EXHIBIT WEAK DENSITY.  RESIDUES 97 - 102
EXHIBIT WEAK DENSITY AND MAY BE IN MULTIPLE CONFORMATIONS.
RESIDUES 315 - 333 EXHIBIT ANISOTROPIC ELECTRON DENSITY.

RESIDUES 522 - 532 WERE DISORDERED IN THE NATIVE STRUCTURE
(5EAS) BUT DISPLAY STRONG DENSITY IN THE FARNESYL
HYDROXYPHOSPHONATE COMPLEX.  RESIDUES 253 - 266 ARE BETTER
ORDERED THAN IN THE NATIVE STRUCTURE, AND HAVE TRANSLATED
2-3 ANGSTROMS TOWARD THE ACTIVE SITE.
;
_refine.pdbx_starting_model                      'NATIVE TEAS (PDB ENTRY 5EAS)' 
_refine.pdbx_method_to_determine_struct          'RIGID BODY REFINEMENT/DIFFERENCE FOURIER MAPS' 
